on her mobile phone, saying that internal 
affairs officers were beating her, that they had 
&#8220;broken [her] spine&#8221; and that her &#8220;back hurt&#8221;. 
According to the video recordings taken in 
the entrance hall of the district police station, 
Ms. Polyakova sat on the floor for at least 35 
minutes. During this time, she was on 
numerous occasions invited to stand up, but 
she continued to sit there until the arrival of a 
new ambulance crew. 
</p>
<p>The forensic medical report concluded that 
apart from the bruise on her forehead referred 
to above, there were no signs of injury on Ms. 
Polyakova&#8217;s body.The Salihorsk district 
procurator&#8217;s office on 27 November 2008 
decided not to institute criminal proceedings 
against the officers, for lack of evidence that 
a crime had been committed. Ms. Polyakova 
failed to appear at procurators&#8217; offices when 
she was summoned by them. The Office of 
