<p>19.   11/12/09 JUA CAM; 
TOR 
</p>
<p><b>Concerning a group of 22 ethnic-Uyghurs of 
Chinese nationality currently awaiting 
refugee status determination</b> by the United 
Nations High Commissioner for Refugees 
(UNHCR) and the Cambodian authorities. 
</p>
<p>A group of 22 members of the Uyghur minority 
are seeking asylum in Cambodia after fleeing 
the clashes between Uyghurs and Han Chinese, 
which took place in the Xinjiang region in July 
</p><p>2009. These clashes resulted in numerous 
people, including many Uyghurs, being detained 
and severely tortured by the police and the 
military police. Many others were also killed 
during these events. 
</p>
<p>The 22 persons have all registered for asylum at 
UNHCR in Phnom Penh, and have received 
&#8220;Persons of Concern&#8221; letters. Only one of them 
has been interviewed. The Ministry of Interior, 
for its part, has indicated that they would be 
returned to their point of entry if they did not 
have any legal documents.<b> 
</b></p>
