<p><b>Mr. Huang Fajun</b>, resident of Acheng District, 
Harbin City, Heilongjiang Province. On 24 July 
2007, policemen from the Sougfengshan Town 
Police Station arrested Mr. Huang and beat him 
until both of his feet broke. The police detained 
him in the Acheng District First Detention 
Centre. He went on a hunger strike to protest the 
detention and was force-fed. He developed open 
sores, and his hands and feet were swollen and 
showed deep scars caused by shackles and cuffs. 
On 2 November 2007, the police notified his 
family that he was dying and that they could 
visit him at the Archeng District Traditional 
Medicine Hospital. He was allowed to return 
home on 4 November 2007, where he died at 
around 8 p.m. on 6 November 2007.  
</p>
<p><b>Mr. Xiong Zhengming</b>.<b> </b>On 15 March 2007, 
police officers took Xiong Zhengming to the 
Wanyuan City First Detention Center, indicating 
that they had detected that Mr. Xiong visited 
overseas websites. Following eight months of 
detention, the police sentenced Mr. Xiong to one 
year of forced labour. Later, he was transferred 
to the Wanyuan City Second Detention Center. 
On 3 December 2007, he was informed of a 
