Kazakhstan. However, his asylum claim in the 
Czech Republic was recently rejected and the 
conclusions of the migration service of the 
Czech Republic, which made a decision on his 
deportation, reportedly failed to take into 
account that four of his Muslim associates who 
stayed in Kazakhstan were imprisoned under 
falsified charges. Also, some procedural 
violations have been reported, such as incorrect 
translations of interviews, which failed to reflect 
some of the accounts relevant to the asylum 
claims.  
</p>
