the southwestern side of the Kyrgyz 
Republic&#8217;s Government House. Ten minutes 
after, he was detained by officers from the 
Bishkek Central Internal Affairs Department 
and taken to the May Day district police 
station in Bishkek. Within three hours, the 
evidence concerning his case was transferred 
for review to the May Day district court. The 
court found Mr. Kuleshov guilty of having 
committed an administrative offence and was 
fined.  
</p>
