Cotabato Provincial jail in Amas, Kidapawan 
City. The soldiers who took him to jail forced 
him to sign some documents which were not 
explained to him. The soldiers also cited 1 April 
as the date of arrest and not 9 January.  
</p>
<p>Mr. Salih is currently on trial in connection with 
a bombing incident in Kidapawan City, and 
although his trial is taking place in North 
Cotabato Province, he was transferred to a jail in 
Bicutan, Metro Manila, as he is considered a 
high-risk detainee. </p>

