Headquarters received a petition concerning 
the legality of Mr. Bogushevsky&#8217;s detention, 
the investigation of the criminal case and the 
use of pressure against him to obtain a 
confession. On 17 June, the Internal Security 
Service conducted a judicial inquiry into the 
claims, but the facts alleged could not be 
objectively verified. The Office of the 
Attorney-General of the Russian Federation is 
currently conducting an inquiry into the 
legality of and the justification for the 
decision not to prosecute the police officers. </p>

