persons were sent to the Inkayuth Army 
Camp, on 21 March for further inquiry. After 
having been interrogated by officials, they 
were released on 9 April due to a lack of 
evidence. Regarding the allegation of torture, 
no petition or complaint was filed by or on 
behalf of Mr. Salae. </p>

