<p><b>362</b> Para Country Date Type Mandate Allegations transmitted Government response 
was diagnosed, treatment was delayed with 
reference to lack of space in the hospital 
dormitory and the &#8220;queue&#8221; of prisoners awaiting 
treatment. As a result, the cancer spread and has 
become life-threatening.  
</p>
<p>In spite of a report by forensic medical doctors 
of Cukurova University in Adana dated 22 June 
2009, which indicated that Ms. Zere was in need 
of hospitalization and that her life was in danger, 
she has not been released from detention and is 
unable to access adequate medical treatment. 
</p>
<p>A complaint against the Prison prosecutor of 
Elbistan has been filed, however, to no avail. 
