feeding tube is essential to his survival and 
needs to be guarded against infection by being 
cleaned daily after each meal.  
</p>
<p>Mr. Pierre is facing deportation to Haiti, without 
having at his disposal any further recourse to the 
U.S. courts system. It is alleged that, if 
transferred to Haiti as a criminal deportee, he 
would be detained, which means that he might 
be subjected to dehydration, starvation, and 
infection via his feeding tube, since it is unclear 
whether basic hygiene provisions would be 
fulfilled.  
</p>
